urls.title: Brazil Bow Out & England's Date With Destiny!
urls.description: Listen to this episode from GameDay on Spotify. Sam Matterface is joined by talkSPORT's Football Correspondent Alex Crook and European Football Expert Kevin Hatchard to look back at yesterday's World Cup quarter-finals. Brazil bow out of the tournament after a penalty shoot-out defeat to Croatia, who continue to defy the odds by qualifying for back-to-back World Cup semi-finals. They also discuss Argentina's shootout victory over the Netherlands in the other quarter-final, and preview a huge game for England against the World Champions France - live on talkSPORT tonight! Hosted on Acast. See acast.com/privacy for more information.

urls.title: FIFA could abandon 3-team groups for 2026 World Cup
urls.description: Arsene Wenger, FIFA's chief of global football, says a final decision has not yet been made on the format for the 2026 World Cup.

tweets.text:
Arsene Wenger says FIFA is considering 3 possible formats for the 2026 World Cup

1) 16 groups of 3, top  2 go through 
2) 12 group of 4, top 2 + 8 3rd go through
3) 6 groups of 4 in two halves of 24, meeting in a final (ie, like two Euros converging)

https://t.co/F8t0OIgiDz
